{"timestamp": "2025-12-02 15:28:00.515846", "event": "llm_end", "text": "Troubleshooting diagnosis report — multi-tier Clos EBGP fabric\nSummary\n- Current network shows one isolated host subnet: 10.0.0.0/24 (pc_0_0). That prefix is not present in the fabric routing tables and other hosts cannot reach pc_0_0.\n- The immediate cause is BGP session failures between leaf_router_0_0 and the spines. Those failed sessions prevent leaf_router_0_0 from advertising 10.0.0.0/24 into the EBGP fabric.\n- Root cause: leaf_router_0_0 is misconfigured with an incorrect local BGP AS (65800) that does not match the expected AS (65200) used by its spine peers; this leads to its BGP neighbors remaining in Idle and no prefix propagation.\n\nEvidence and findings (collected outputs)\n1) End-host reachability (summary)\n- Many cross-pod pings to 10.0.0.2 (pc_0_0) are listed as \"unknown\" / not successful in the reachability matrix, while other subnets are reachable. Example from the reachability output:\n  - Multiple src hosts (pc_1_3, pc_1_1, pc_1_0, etc.) show status \"unknown\" when destination is pc_0_0 (10.0.0.2), while other destinations show successful pings with 0% loss.\n\n2) leaf_router_0_0: running config / BGP config\n- Running config shows leaf_router_0_0 configured as:\n  - \"router bgp 65800\" (local AS 65800)\n  - BGP neighbors configured toward spine addresses (172.16.0.32, .40, .48, .56)\n  - Prefix to advertise: \"network 10.0.0.0/24\"\n- However the AS number is 65800 (unexpected compared to other leaves/spines).\n\n3) leaf_router_0_0: BGP session state\n- show ip bgp summary on leaf_router_0_0:\n  - All neighbors are in State \"Idle\" and PfxRcd/PfxSnt = 0\n  - Example lines:\n    - 172.16.0.32 ... State/PfxRcd: Idle\n    - 172.16.0.40 ... State/PfxRcd: Idle\n  - This indicates the BGP TCP/session did not reach Established — therefore no BGP routes from this leaf are learned by spines.\n\n4) spine router view of leaf_router_0_0 sessions\n- spine_router_0_0 show ip bgp summary:\n  - It has neighbor 172.16.0.33 configured as remote-as 65200 and that neighbor is in State \"Idle\" (Neighbor = 172.16.0.33 corresponds to leaf_router_0_0).\n  - Example: Neighbor 172.16.0.33 ... State/PfxRcd: Idle\n- spine_router_0_1 similarly shows the neighbor that corresponds to leaf_router_0_0 in State \"Idle\".\n- These spines expect the leaf to be in AS 65200 (their neighbor config uses remote-as 65200), but the leaf is advertising itself as AS 65800 in its config.\n\n5) Routing tables: missing prefix 10.0.0.0/24\n- spine_router_0_0, spine_router_0_1, and super_spine_router_0 BGP/routing outputs show 10.0.1/24, 10.0.2/24, 10.0.3/24, and 10.1.* networks learned, but no 10.0.0.0/24 entry is present in their tables (i.e., the 10.0.0.0/24 route is absent).\n- leaf_router_0_1 (the other leaf) does have its 10.0.1.0/24 locally connected and BGP working; this contrasts with leaf_router_0_0’s isolation.\n\nLocalization (affected devices)\n- Primary faulty device: leaf_router_0_0\n  - Symptom: BGP sessions with all spine neighbors are Idle; not exchanging prefixes.\n  - Effect: 10.0.0.0/24 (pc_0_0) is not advertised and is unreachable from the rest of the fabric.\n- Impacted devices/flows:\n  - pc_0_0 (10.0.0.2) is isolated from other pods and from the super-spine/spine fabric.\n  - Spines and super-spine do not have route to 10.0.0.0/24 and therefore cannot forward traffic to pc_0_0.\n\nRoot cause analysis\n- The core misconfiguration is the incorrect BGP local AS on leaf_router_0_0:\n  - leaf_router_0_0 is configured \"router bgp 65800\".\n  - Spines are configured to peer with AS 65200 for the corresponding leaf (spine expects neighbor at 172.16.0.33 to be ASN 65200).\n  - The AS mismatch prevents the BGP sessions from progressing to Established (neighbors remain Idle).\n- Because BGP sessions are down, the leaf cannot advertise its directly-connected host subnet (10.0.0.0/24) into the EBGP fabric. Thus the prefix is absent from the global routing tables and hosts in other pods cannot reach pc_0_0.\n\nSeverity / impact\n- High for the local tenant or service on 10.0.0.0/24: the host pc_0_0 is fully isolated from the rest of the network.\n- Medium for the fabric: only one leaf is affected; other leaves and the spine/super-spine remain operational and carry their prefixes.\n\nRelevant excerpts (supporting CLI lines)\n- leaf_router_0_0 running config: \"router bgp 65800\" (local AS = 65800)\n- leaf_router_0_0 BGP summary: neighbors 172.16.0.32/.40/.48/.56 — State = Idle, PfxRcd = 0\n- spine_router_0_0 BGP summary: neighbor 172.16.0.33 remote-as 65200 — State = Idle\n- Routing tables (spine / super): 10.0.0.0/24 absent (other 10.0.x/24 present)\n\nConclusion\n- The network health is degraded but localized: one leaf (leaf_router_0_0) has a BGP configuration error (wrong local AS) causing BGP session failures and preventing advertisement of its host subnet (10.0.0.0/24). This explains the observed reachability failures for pc_0_0. No other broad fabric failures were observed — other leaves and spines have established BGP sessions and are carrying their prefixes.\n\nNote: I have not performed any remediation actions. If you want, I can (on request) enumerate the exact config mismatches, show the minimal diffs, or collect any additional logs/outputs to further corroborate timing/sequence of failures.", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 13975, "output_tokens": 3237, "total_tokens": 17212, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 13568}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 1728}}}
